


	Fndnxt   finds the next occurence of the search string as
		defined in FIND.  This applies to either the forward
		or backup direction.

	FIND   will prompt you for the desired search string and then
        find it in either the forward or reverse direction.
   			Press FIND, enter the desired string, and press
			return.  you must have selected which direction
		    prior to pressing FIND or it will search in the
		   	current direction.


To return to the keypad diagram, press the Help key (PF2).
For help on another keypad key, press that key.
To exit from help, type a space.
